comments: Porter Jr. (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Crowder (PHX).
Ayton (PHX) jumps into Wood (HOU) and makes contact with his body prior to getting to the ball during the rebound.
At the start of the drive, Crowder (PHX) places a hand/arm to Porter Jr.'s (HOU) front and affects his SQBR.
Olynyk (HOU) reaches in and makes contact to Paul's (PHX) arm that disrupts his dribble.
Wood (HOU) is in the lane for about 3 seconds when a foul is imminently whistled.
Ayton (PHX) moves towards Wood (HOU) and brings his arms down from a vertical position to make contact with Wood's arm during his driving shot attempt.

Ayton (PHX) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot to try and create distance from the ball pressure. Any contact to Ayton's arm by Olynyk (HOU) or Tate (HOU) during their attempt to tie the ball up is deemed marginal.
Ayton (PHX) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Wood (HOU) at the end of his drive.
Crowder (PHX) grabs and pulls Olynyk's (HOU) jersey shorts away from his body, which restricts his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Crowder (PHX) and Olynyk (HOU) engage and disengage off ball in the post and the contact is marginal.
Olynyk (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position on Booker (PHX) and cleanly deflects the pass away.
During the drive to the basket, Tate (HOU) makes contact to Booker's (PHX) body and the contact affects his SQBR.
During the pick, Paul (PHX) and Wood (HOU) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
During the post-up, Paul (PHX) wraps Wood (HOU) and the contact affects his SQBR.
Paul (PHX) starts his move towards the basket and marginal contact occurs when he briefly places his hand on Porter Jr.'s (HOU) leg.
Bradley (HOU) legally contests Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
During the inbounds, Porter Jr. (HOU) releases the pass within 5 seconds.
Craig (PHX) commits a take foul on Wood (HOU).
Bradley (HOU) commits a take foul on Booker (PHX).
Booker (PHX) maintains a legal guarding position on Olynyk (HOU) and cleanly deflects away the inbounds pass.
